### 5. `emitToolCall` — handler ordering

**File**: `/Users/shivam94/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent/dist/core/extensions/runner.js` (lines 620-648)

```javascript
async emitToolCall(event) {
    const ctx = this.createContext();
    let result;
    for (const ext of this.extensions) {          // ← iterates ALL extensions
        const handlers = ext.handlers.get("tool_call");
        if (!handlers || handlers.length === 0)
            continue;
        for (const handler of handlers) {          // ← ALL handlers for this extension
            const handlerResult = await handler(event, ctx);
            if (handlerResult) {                    // truthy check
                result = handlerResult;
                if (result.block) {                 // { block: true } short-circuits
                    return result;
                }
            }
        }
    }
    return result;
}
```

**Key rules:**
- Iterates extensions in registration order
- For each extension, iterates all its `tool_call` handlers
- First `{ block: true }` wins (short-circuits)
- `undefined` or falsy = continues to next handler/extension
- If no handler returns `{ block: true }`, returns last truthy result (or `undefined`)

